      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here is the implementation of `detect_arbitrage` optimized for performance using a sliding window approach:\n\n```python\nimport time\n\ndef detect_arbitrage(ticks):\n    for i in range(1, len(ticks)):\n        diff = abs(ticks[i][1] - ticks[i-1][1])\n        if diff > 0.05:\n            delta_time = ticks[i][0] - ticks[i-1][0]\n            if delta_time <= 10 and i == len(ticks) - 1:\n                return True\n            # Iterate backward to find the last tick within the 10ms window\n            for j in range(i-1, -1, -1):\n                if ticks[i][0] - ticks[j][0] > 10:\n                    break # Window violated\n                if abs(ticks[i][1] - ticks[j][1]) > 0.05:\n                    return True # Found valid signal\n    return False\n```\n\nThis function iterates linearly through the input list, calculating price differences and timestamps immediately to avoid storing intermediate state. It prioritizes the consecutive check for speed before expanding the",
